    <div class="container" id="privacy-policy">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

        <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
        <p><strong>HowManyOfMe</strong> is a free statistical name-based search website that provides estimated counts of how many people share a given name in the United States. We value your privacy and take our obligations seriously, even though we do not directly collect any personal data from our visitors.</p>

        <h2>2. What Data We Do Not Collect</h2>
        <p>We do <strong>not</strong> collect or store:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Names or identity information entered into the search form</li>
            <li>IP addresses</li>
            <li>Browser user-agent strings</li>
            <li>Location data</li>
            <li>Email addresses or form submissions</li>
        </ul>
        <p>All searches are processed anonymously and in real-time. No data is stored or logged on our servers.</p>

        <h2>3. Google AdSense and Third-Party Cookies</h2>
        <p>This site displays ads served by <strong>Google AdSense</strong>. Google may use cookies, web beacons, or similar technologies to collect or receive information about your visit to display personalized ads.</p>
        <p>Google may use this data to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Deliver ads tailored to your interests</li>
            <li>Measure ad performance and user interaction</li>
            <li>Prevent fraudulent or invalid activity</li>
        </ul>
        <p>You can manage your ad personalization preferences or opt out by visiting:</p>
        <p>
            <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
                https://www.google.com/settings/ads
            </a><br />
            <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
                Google Ads Privacy Policy
            </a>
        </p>

        <h2>4. Do Not Track & Analytics</h2>
        <p>We do <strong>not</strong> use Google Analytics or any other user tracking services. We also do not respond to Do Not Track (DNT) signals since we do not track users in any way.</p>

        <h2>5. Data Sharing and Sale</h2>
        <p>We do not share, sell, rent, or trade any data because we do not collect any user data. Any ad-related activity is strictly handled by Google or their authorized ad partners.</p>

        <h2>6. Cookies Policy</h2>
        <p>We ourselves do not set any cookies. However, third-party advertisers (like Google AdSense) may place cookies in your browser for ad personalization. You can disable cookies in your browser settings if you prefer not to receive personalized ads.</p>

        <h2>7. Compliance with Privacy Laws</h2>
        <p>We strive to comply with all major privacy regulations:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR):</strong> No user data is processed or stored.</li>
            <li><strong>California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA):</strong> No personal data is sold or stored, so no opt-out is necessary.</li>
            <li><strong>Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA):</strong> This site is not intended for children under 13. No data is knowingly collected from children.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>8. Third-Party Links</h2>
        <p>Our website may include links to other websites. We are not responsible for the privacy policies or practices of those sites. We recommend reviewing their policies directly.</p>

        <h2>9. Policy Updates</h2>
        <p>This privacy policy may be updated occasionally to reflect changes in technology or legal requirements. Any updates will be posted on this page with an updated effective date.</p>

        <h2>10. Contact Information</h2>
        <p>If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us</p>
